Adult.name: Adult
Adult.defination: An age group comprised of individuals who have reached sexual maturity but whose character and personality are still developing. In psychology this generally covers the age range of 20-40

Adults.name: Adult
Adults.defination: An age group comprised of individuals who have reached sexual maturity but whose character and personality are still developing. In psychology this generally covers the age range of 20-40

Juvenile.name: Juvenile
Juvenile.defination: The stage of being no more dependent of the nest and/or from caregivers for subsistence while having not reach sexual maturity.

Adult, reproductively mature.name: Adult, reproductively mature
Adult, reproductively mature.defination: An age group comprised of humans who have reached reproductive age

Fetal to Parturition.name: Fetal to Parturition
Fetal to Parturition.defination: period (day/month) during which female animals give birth (in relation to their natural sexual season) (fr)

Nursing Child.name: Nursing Child
Nursing Child.defination: An age group comprised of individuals between one month and two years of age

During brain development.name: During brain development
During brain development.defination: Development, taking place during the embryonic phase, of a tissue or tissues that work together to perform a specific function or functions. Development pertains to the process whose specific outcome is the progression of a structure over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Organs are commonly observed as visibly distinct structures, but may also exist as loosely associated clusters of cells that work together to perform a specific function or functions

All life stages.name: All life stages
All life stages.defination: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's expected maximum age

Development.name: Development
Development.defination: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an embryo from its formation until the end of its embryonic life stage. The end of the embryonic stage is organism-specific. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

Foetal.name: Foetal
Foetal.defination: Prenatal stage that starts with the fully formed embryo and ends at birth.

Fetal.name: Foetal
Fetal.defination: Prenatal stage that starts with the fully formed embryo and ends at birth.

Embryo.name: Embryo
Embryo.defination: Prenatal stage that starts with fertilization and ends with a fully formed embryo, before undergoing last development during the fetal stage.

Conception to < Fetal.name: Conception to < Fetal
Conception to < Fetal.defination: Onset prior to birth but after 8 weeks of embryonic development (corresponding to a gestational age of 10 weeks).

Pregnancy.name: Pregnancy
Pregnancy.defination: The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth.

During development and at adulthood.name: During development and at adulthood
During development and at adulthood.normalized_term: Status of progression of development in young adulthood

Perinatal.name: Perinatal
Perinatal.defination: The period spanning the range immediately before and after birth.

1 to < 3 months.name: 1 to < 3 months
1 to < 3 months.defination: Infant stage that refers to an infant who is over 2 and under 3 months old.

3 to < 6 months.name: 3 to < 6 months
3 to < 6 months.description: Infant stage that refers to an infant who is over 5 and under 6 months old.

Birth to < 1 month.name: Birth to < 1 month
Birth to < 1 month.description: Infant stage that refers to an infant who is over 1 and under 2 months old.

During brain development, adulthood and.name: During brain development, adulthood and aging

before or during gonadal sex differentia.name: before or during gonadal sex differentiation
before or during gonadal sex differentia.defination: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the gonad over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The gonad is an animal organ that produces gametes; in some species it also produces hormones.
